    "en": {
      "title": "A group from Japan to lend a hand to Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Japan hopes to organize a meeting of Sri Lanka's creditors, which it hopes will help resolve Sri Lanka's debt crisis.",
        "In order to rescue Sri Lanka from the worst debt crisis, Tokyo is open to hold talks between all the creditor countries.",
        "But it is not clear whether China, which owns nearly 20 percent of Sri Lanka's total debt, will join it.",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe told Reuters last week that Sri Lanka would ask Japan to invite major creditor nations to talks on bilateral debt restructuring."
      ],
